properties.author: Christoph Becker, Andreas Rauber
properties.name: Plan for electronic papers
properties.description: This is a DEMO plan for the user 'admin'. This is an example plan. The project was created for the DELOS Summer School 2008 and revised afterwards.

basis.applyingPolicies: No policies have to be applied. The paper which is used for the test is provided by the workshop organizer.
basis.designatedCommunity: Participants of group exercises of the DELOS Summer School
basis.mandate: The purpose is to learn about potential effects of migration tools on documents. To do this we use material available and test various tools that are suitable for this purpose and check the effects on the resulting documents. Conclusions that can be drawn from these experiments are discussed.
basis.organisationalProcedures: No relevant organisational procedures and workflows are available in this example scenario.
basis.planningPurpose: Research Papers in PDF should be converted to a different format, to test the effects of various migration tools on properties of the original document.
basis.planRelations: No previous preservation plans for this purpose exist, so there are no relations to other plans.
basis.preservationRights: As this is just an example preservation plan, no rights for preservation have to be considered. A license for Adobe Acrobat is available.

trigger.description: This plan is created for a new collection of objects.

recommendation.reasoning: The object characteristics are preserved better in the PDF/A than in the HTML format, Adobe Acrobat is eliminated on multiplication, as the process takes too long for the large amount of files that have to be treated in this situation.
